<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFA3FFB0C6F453BCFD08FC99" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA3FFB0C6F453BCFD08FC99" blockId="23.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA3FFB0C6F453BCFEB6FD09" bold="true" box="[199,315,655,681]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFA3FFB0C45E53BCFCB1FD09" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[621,828,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shennongjianus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA3FFB0C45E53BCFCB1FD09" box="[621,828,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">P. shennongjianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA3FFB0C57653BCFC2CFD09" bold="true" box="[837,929,655,681]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFA3FFB0C57653BCFC2CFD09" box="[837,929,655,681]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, it differs from the latter by brownish body colour, longer apical seta of palpus and without small sclerotized pieces behind main sterniteVI. In the key to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFA3FFB0C6A453E4FEABFD51" baseAuthorityName="Disney &amp; Withers" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[151,294,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA3FFB0C6A453E4FEABFD51" box="[151,294,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Pseudacteon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the Russian Far East (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFA3FFB0C40F53E4FC29FD51" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[572,932,727,753]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">Disney &amp; Michailovskaya 2000</bibRefCitation>
), the species runs to couplet 4, to the putative female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFA3FFB0C73453C8FDFCFCB5" authority="Michailovskaya, 1995" authorityName="Disney et Michailovskaya" authorityYear="1995" box="[263,625,762,789]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pullum">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA3FFB0C73453C8FEFDFCB5" box="[263,368,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">P. pullum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFA3FFB0C74553C8FDFCFCB5" author="Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[374,625,762,789]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref22359" refString="Michailovskaya, M. V. (1995) A review of the Eastern Palaearctic species of the genus Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae). Far Eastern Entomologist, Vladivostok, 18, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1995">Michailovskaya, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is different from the latter in having the continuous sternite VI and a palisade extending 3/4 length of mid tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
